    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1893-10-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1893-10-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="118" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d118">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Gresham</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Bayard</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1893-10-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 3,
                            1893</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Yours of September 20 received. Lord Rosebery’s suggestion has been carefully
                        considered, and the President still prefers that all negotiations for
                        concurrent action by the two Governments necessary to <pb facs="0126" n="120" xml:id="pg_120"/> make the award and recommendations of the
                        Bering Sea Tribunal effective be conducted by you at London, and my
                        instructions cabled September 16 are repeated.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
